*                          DS_CRANE.SIZ
*
*       To generate the loads on the rigid frame caused by cranes it 
*       is necessary to know certain facts about the crane system 
*       being used. These fact are not always available from the 
*       customer. This file provides reasonable estimates for the 
*       necessary crane parameters.
*
*       The first three columns are used to select the crane by 
*       listing the crane type, capacity, and span. The next five 
*       columns report information on the crane that is used in the 
*       calculation of crane loads. The program selection is first 
*       based on the crane type and then that set of data which is 
*       nearest to the specified capacity and span. 
*
*       CRANE TYPE:  TG = Top Run Girder
*                    UG = Underhung Girder
*                    MR = Mono Rail
*                    SG = Single Gantry
*
*                                                   RAIL BEAM DEAD LOAD
*CRANE  CAPACITY  SPAN  --WEIGHT, KN----   WHEEL    --- KN PER METER --
*TYPE     KN       mm   BRIDGE  HST & TR  BASE,mm  6000mm BAY 7500mm BAY

